    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation to discerning Nahum's intent in his original context and the chapter's canonical function. The movements below trace the argument from the ironic taunt through the battle vision to the divine oracle. Where the Hebrew vocabulary changes the shade of an English word, a brief note supplements the exposition.",
